### EXISTING STRUCTURES

### Electricity generator at position(52.5, 51.5)
Consists of the following entities:
- Steam engine (position 52.5, 51.5)
- Small electric pole (position 50.5, 50.5)
- Pipe connections (position 51.5, 48.5 and position 52.5, 48.5)

### ERROR TIPS

### Errors related to undefined names
- Ensure that all necessary libraries and modules are properly imported and defined before executing functions. The error "NameError: name 'builtins' is not defined" indicates that there may be a missing import or definition.

### Errors when inserting items into entities
- Verify that the target entity can accept the item being inserted. The error "Failed to insert coal into steam engine" suggests that the steam engine may not have available space or may not accept the item. Check the entity's status and available inventory space before attempting to insert items.

### Errors when checking connections
- Ensure that the connections to the steam engine are properly established. The repeated error "not connected to power network" and "no input liquid" indicates that the steam engine is not connected to a valid power source or fluid input. Check the connections and ensure they are correctly set up.
